Job Description:
Following and enforcing the company's policies and procedures.
Business support: Review contracts related to Bangladesh business, support payment needs of business departments, in-depth business docking, familiar with compliance requirements, identify financial and tax risks, and issue financial and tax solutions for new models and new needs;
Budget preparation: Prepare annual budget, semi-annual budget, budget adjustment, rolling forecast, etc.
Provide professional support to the business team from a financial perspective to drive the business to achieve goals;
Financial analysis: Provide multi-dimensional business analysis reports, such as gross profit by product, income statement, etc., and output risk tips and suggestions;
Able to provide timely financial solutions or foreseeable suggestions to the problems or needs faced by the business department.
Assist employees with benefit inquiries and claims.
Any other task given by the authority.

The Electro Mechanical Engineer will be responsible for all the tasks associated with the investigation, design, installations, commissioning and testing of the electro mechanical equipment’s and systems in improvement project. The specific tasks will include:

Conduct regular inspection of electro mechanical system & equipment as well as necessary production and utility machineries trouble shooting according to the requirement;
Prepare preventive maintenance schedule and ensure implementation accordingly;
Participate and supervise the installation, commission & validation of machineries/equipment as per standard;
Collect design and operational data of the existing electro mechanical equipment’s / systems and review their operational performances, and make recommendations for the operational efficiency improvements;
Carry out electromechanical equipment’s / systems installation designs, installation plans and supervise the drafting of the design drawings;
Prepare works progress reports and contract close-out reports;
Training of the water corporation staff on operation and maintenance tasks, and records keeping;
Review the electromechanical assets / systems operational performances produce reports and follow up on any warranty maintenance as required. Age 32 to 40 years
Additional certifications in project management or relevant mechanical systems will be an advantage.
Proficient in using standard software tools for mechanical engineering and maintenance.
Excellent communication and decision-making abilities.
Familiarity with industry safety standards and regulations.

Age 26 to 35 years
Verified Experience should be at least 3 years.
Comprehensive knowledge in drawing development (2D and 3D in AutoCAD,
Strong communication skills in English (written and oral),
Good technical skills, Shall be responsible for Electrical and Information Technology activities.
It is mandatory to submit original certificates (i.e: BSc, HSC, SSC) and experience certificate to get the job. To follow up all designs, drawings and specifications according to the project Standards;
To supervise, monitor and ensure overall quality of construction works including finishing works and the quality of materials being used at respective projects as per the specifications;
To be responsible for preparing work plans and periodical reports for ongoing projects;
To be responsible for solving any construction-related problems in consultation with the consultants, if necessary, that arise at the project sites;
To be responsible for liaising with Head Office, other professionals within design teams (consultants) and contractors; representatives during construction;
To be responsible for the preparation of Engineering Documents and other documental works for the construction of ongoing projects and maintain the same;
To be responsible for attending meetings and competently communicating with Head Office, Contractors and major asset owners and stakeholders;
To be responsible for managing, directing and monitoring progress during each phase of a project;
To be responsible for taking measurements of the finished works for running bills and recording those in MBs (Measurement Books);
To be responsible for checking the final MBs for final payment and refunding security deposit with the commendation;
To be responsible for preparing the drawings with specifications and BoQ for special items of renovation works;
To have to be computer-literate and conversant with MS Office suite and relevant engineering software packages;
To have to be fluent in writing technical reports, e-mailing and internet browsing;
To have to assume any other responsibility and maintain any other register as assigned by the management.
To be responsible for any tangible or intangible loss or damage caused to the property or interest of the employing organization due to your negligence of duty, unprofessional activity or moral turpitude.
